  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain sectors are typically required to:\n\n1. Implement anti-money laundering (AML) compliance programs\n2. Conduct customer due diligence\n3. Report suspicious transactions to financial intelligence units\n4. Maintain transaction records\n5. Verify customer identities\n6. Train employees to recognize potential money laundering activities\n\nSpecific reporting requirements vary by jurisdiction, but generally involve filing suspicious activity reports (SARs) with designated authorities.\n\nWould you like me to provide more details about money laundering reporting requirements?",
